<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Editor(s). (Ed[s].). (Year of publication). <em>Title of book</em>. Publisher.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Editor(s)">Craven, I.</span> (Ed.). 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2001</span>). 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of book">Australian cinema in the 1990s</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Frank Cass</span>.
</blockquote>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Editor(s)">Smith, A., &amp;  Brown, B.</span> (Eds.). 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2017</span>). 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of book">Sustainability in practice: Overcoming energy challenges in the 21st century</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Northwoods Press</span>.
</blockquote>
